<div id="review_84798868" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/84798868" />
    <a title="Dxmaniac69" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3089339-dxmaniac69"><img alt="Dxmaniac69" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/84798868?book_show_action=true">Jan 13, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dxmaniac69" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dxmaniac69" href="/user/show/3089339-dxmaniac69">Dxmaniac69</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9782266126076" href="/book/show/19586.Mystery">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer84798868" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12689627671435477786">The second book in the Blue Rose trilogy, but if you happen to read it by itself it&apos;s no big deal. The book stands alone perfectly well and you won&apos;t even notice how it ties into the first book, Koko, until about 3/4ths of the way thru. And even then the tie in is minor.<br/><br/>The book is a tense thriller and sort of a horror novel. There is only a slight illusion to anything supernatural, but like Koko the horror in this series comes from the depths humanity will sink too.<br/><br/>I&apos;d actually give this book a</span>
  <span id="freeText12689627671435477786" style="display:none">The second book in the Blue Rose trilogy, but if you happen to read it by itself it's no big deal. The book stands alone perfectly well and you won't even notice how it ties into the first book, Koko, until about 3/4ths of the way thru. And even then the tie in is minor.<br /><br />The book is a tense thriller and sort of a horror novel. There is only a slight illusion to anything supernatural, but like Koko the horror in this series comes from the depths humanity will sink too.<br /><br />I'd actually give this book a rating of 4 1/2 stars. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12689627671435477786" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

